  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin fries</p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to the tray[s] with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708352216535-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708352216535-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708352216535-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708352216535-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708352216535-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are in the oven, slice your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Add the <strong>hake pieces</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> to a bowl and give everything a good mix up then set aside</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to a shallow plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>herby mixture</strong></p><p>Tip: For a spicier burger, go heavy on the black pepper!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708352218802-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708352218802-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708352218802-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708352218802-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708352218802-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>hake pieces</strong> from the bowl and firmly press each one into the <strong>herby mixture</strong>,<strong> </strong>making sure to evenly coat them on both sides – these are your <strong>coated hake goujons</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708352222259-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708352222259-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708352222259-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708352222259-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708352222259-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated hake goujons</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden brown, crispy and cooked through – this is your<strong> crispy fried hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked through when it's opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
